A wide variety of things can be done to protect our environment. One of the things that can be done is to make the existing road vehicles more fuel efficient. Nearly all petrol vehicles that are on the roads today are suitable to have LPG systems installed. LPG is a cleaner and cheaper fuel. Petrol will still be needed to start the engine but then the LPG system will soon activate. The rate of petrol consumption will reduce which will cut emissions and still benefit the environment. Hybrid cars, electric cars and even hydrogen powered cars are all good too.

If you are worried about the future, the only way to feel better is to act.
Try to use less plastic, don't throw rubbish in the WC, recycle, use a bit less electricity...there are plenty of things you can do to avoid all of this and you can see them in a lot of web pages.

Maybe you can't follow every step, but if you do some of them you are contributing to make a better future for everyone, including you.
Don't forget to live your life with happiness. Do things you like like using electronic devices, buy products for fun etc, but also, you wil find a great feeling of joy if you contribute to all of this.

Be happy and let everyone in the future be happy too.

You video ignored the contribution of agriculture - specifically the western intensive farming methods. This consumes large amounts of energy and resources to produce ever larger amounts of meat. Agriculture, forestry and land-use change contributed around 20 to 25% to global annual emissions.

As such your video fails to provide the full picture because (of course) acknowledging that clean power alone is not going to save us wouldn't make for a nice ending right ?
